<text top="75" left="83" width="610" height="54" font="4">Why Behave Professionally?</text>
<text top="157" left="66" width="907" height="35" font="5">We (Computer Scientists) are judged internally (invisibly) by it as </text>
<text top="195" left="66" width="146" height="35" font="5">individuals</text>
<text top="233" left="66" width="787" height="35" font="5">• All members of a group (including you) are judged by </text>
<text top="271" left="107" width="128" height="35" font="5">outsiders</text>
<text top="346" left="66" width="889" height="35" font="5">Professional behaviour enhances prestige of group, and you by </text>
<text top="384" left="66" width="157" height="35" font="5">association</text>
<text top="460" left="66" width="874" height="35" font="5">Doctors, nurses and lawyers are generally respected in society</text>
<text top="498" left="66" width="858" height="35" font="5">• Current standing of journalists and politicians are a decent </text>
<text top="535" left="107" width="232" height="35" font="5">counter example</text>
</page>
