<text top="75" left="83" width="424" height="54" font="4">Professional Bodies</text>
<text top="156" left="66" width="526" height="37" font="6">UK: <i>British Computer Society (BCS)</i></text>
<text top="195" left="66" width="734" height="37" font="6">US:  <i>Association for Computing Machinery (ACM) </i></text>
<text top="235" left="140" width="795" height="37" font="7"><i>Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers (IEEE)</i></text>
<text top="300" left="66" width="685" height="37" font="6">Bodies provide a range of benefits to members</text>
<text top="339" left="66" width="887" height="37" font="6">• Databases of papers and (surprisingly good) professional </text>
<text top="379" left="107" width="160" height="37" font="6">magazines</text>
<text top="419" left="66" width="284" height="37" font="6">• Training courses</text>
<text top="458" left="66" width="228" height="37" font="6">• Conferences</text>
<text top="498" left="66" width="802" height="37" font="6">• Some employees insist on having, and maintaining, </text>
<text top="537" left="107" width="182" height="37" font="6">membership</text>
</page>
