<text top="73" left="83" width="160" height="54" font="4">Results</text>
<text top="161" left="83" width="459" height="37" font="16"><b>McDanel </b>convicted,	spent	time	in	jail	</text>
<text top="198" left="83" width="10" height="34" font="15">•</text>
<text top="197" left="137" width="574" height="37" font="15">Appealed	after	release	– conviction	overturned</text>
<text top="234" left="83" width="10" height="34" font="15">•</text>
<text top="233" left="137" width="868" height="37" font="18"><i>The	government	charged	and	convicted	McDanel under	the	theory	that	</i></text>
<text top="269" left="137" width="844" height="37" font="18"><i>the	e-mailed	warning	itself	violated	the	anti-hacking	Computer	Fraud	</i></text>
<text top="305" left="137" width="819" height="37" font="18"><i>and	Abuse	Act	because	it	“impaired	the	integrity”	of	the	vulnerable	</i></text>
<text top="341" left="137" width="91" height="37" font="18"><i>system.</i></text>
<text top="402" left="83" width="716" height="37" font="16"><b>Gunn </b>sacked	and	prosecuted	under	the	Official	Secrets	Act</text>
<text top="440" left="83" width="10" height="34" font="15">•</text>
